Mexico Cotton Planted Crop to Rise to 300,000 Hectares by 2016

-- B y   C a r l o s   M a n u e l   R o d r i g u e z
-- 
2011-08-01T13:20:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-01/mexico-cotton-planted-crop-to-rise-to-300-000-hectares-by-2016.html
Mexico  plans to increase the planted
area of cotton by 71 percent to 300,000 hectares (741,000 acres)
by 2016, the  Agriculture Ministry  said.  The country aims to boost the planted area from a
forecasted 175,000 hectares this year, the ministry said in a
statement yesterday. Cotton output will rise to 2.4 million
bales in five years, up from 620,000 bales now, the ministry
said, citing comments from Jorge Antonio Medina, an industry
advisory member.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carlos M. Rodriguez in Mexico City at 
 carlosmr@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at   dcrofts@bloomberg.net  